Lucian Faggiano bought the building in Lecce, Puglia in the south of Italy and planned to turn it into a trattoria . 
  But he discovered a sewage pipe beneath the building was blocked . 
  He and his sons dug underground and found a Messapian tomb built 2,000 years ago . 
  They also found a Roman granary, a Franciscan chapel and etchings from the Knights Templar . 
  The building has now been turned into a museum  . 
 